    "# Region-based Convolutional Neural Network\n",
    "\n",
    "**R-CNN** stands for **Region-based Convolutional Neural Network**.\n",
    "It is a deep learning method for **object detection**, introduced by Ross Girshick and collaborators in 2014.\n",
    "\n",
    "Object detection means:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Finding where objects are** in an image (bounding boxes)\n",
    "2. **Classifying what those objects are**\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, in one image the model may detect:\n",
    "\n",
    "* a dog\n",
    "* a bicycle\n",
    "* a person\n",
    "\n",
    "and **draw boxes** around each object.\n",
    "\n",
    "Before R-CNN, image classification models could say *what* objects existed in an image, but not *where* they were located. R-CNN addressed this by first generating candidate object regions and then classifying each region.\n",
    "\n",
    "Think of R-CNN like this:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Search image for possible objects\n",
    "2. Wrap each possible object to fixed size\n",
    "3. Ask CNN “What is this?”\n",
    "4. Keep best answers\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why R-CNN Was Important\n",
    "\n",
    "Before R-CNN, object detection mostly used:\n",
    "\n",
    "* hand-crafted features(kernel weight defined manually)\n",
    "* sliding windows\n",
    "* traditional machine learning  \n",
    "    Before deep learning, object detection pipelines looked like this:\n",
    "    1. Extract Hand-Crafted Features\n",
    "       * Image → HOG Features\n",
    "    2. Train Classical ML Model  \n",
    "      Use algorithms like:\n",
    "       * SVM (Support Vector Machine)\n",
    "       * Decision Trees\n",
    "       * Random Forest\n",
    "       * AdaBoost\n",
    "\n",
    "R-CNN showed that **CNNs (Convolutional Neural Networks)** could dramatically improve detection accuracy. It became the foundation for later systems:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Fast R-CNN\n",
    "* Faster R-CNN\n",
    "* Mask R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "## Goal of R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Given an image:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Detect objects present\n",
    "* Identify object classes\n",
    "* Predict object locations using bounding boxes\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Input image:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Image: Street scene\n",
    "Contains:\n",
    "- Person\n",
    "- Car\n",
    "- Bicycle\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Desired output:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Person → Bounding box (x1,y1,x2,y2)\n",
    "Car → Bounding box (x1,y1,x2,y2)\n",
    "Bicycle → Bounding box (x1,y1,x2,y2)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "## R-CNN Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "![R-CNN Architecture](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/masum184e/handbook-old/removed/images/cnn/r_cnn.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "The process consists of several stages:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Input image                          \n",
    "2. Region proposal generation\n",
    "    * Selective Search(~2000 region proposals)\n",
    "3. Warp regions to fixed size\n",
    "4. CNN feature extraction\n",
    "5. Classification using SVM\n",
    "6. Bounding-box regression refinement\n",
    "\n",
    "### Region Proposal Generation\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of sliding a window across the entire image at every scale, R-CNN uses **Selective Search**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Selective Search proposes approximately:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "~2000 candidate regions/image\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "These regions are likely to contain objects.\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose we have:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Image size: 500×500\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Selective search may produce:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Region 1: dog candidate\n",
    "Region 2: tree candidate\n",
    "Region 3: wheel candidate\n",
    "...\n",
    "Region 2000\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The purpose is to reduce search space.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### How Selective Search works\n",
    "\n",
    "It groups pixels according to:\n",
    "\n",
    "* color similarity\n",
    "* texture\n",
    "* size\n",
    "* shape compatibility\n",
    "\n",
    "Small regions merge recursively.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Initial segmentation:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "[grass][grass][dog]\n",
    "[grass][dog][dog]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Regions with similar properties merge:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "[grass]\n",
    "[dog]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Bounding boxes around merged regions become proposals.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Warp Candidate Regions\n",
    "\n",
    "CNN requires fixed-size input.\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose CNN accepts:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "227×227\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Candidate regions differ:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Region A: 50×70\n",
    "Region B: 200×300\n",
    "Region C: 120×150\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "All are resized:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "50×70 →227×227\n",
    "200×300→227×227\n",
    "120×150→227×227\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### CNN Feature Extraction\n",
    "\n",
    "Each resized proposal passes through a CNN (originally AlexNet).It outputs feature vectors.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Proposal:\n",
    "dog image patch\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "CNN output:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "[0.32,0.81,0.12,....,0.45]\n",
    "\n",
    "4096-dimensional feature vector\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This vector represents important visual patterns:\n",
    "\n",
    "* edges\n",
    "* corners\n",
    "* textures\n",
    "* shapes\n",
    "\n",
    "### Classification using SVM\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of using CNN softmax directly, original R-CNN trains separate SVM classifiers.\n",
    "\n",
    "For each object class:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Dog SVM\n",
    "Cat SVM\n",
    "Car SVM\n",
    "Person SVM\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose feature vector:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "x=[0.32,0.81,...]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "SVM outputs:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Dog score =0.91\n",
    "Cat score =0.02\n",
    "Car score =0.10\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Prediction:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Dog\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Bounding Box Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "The proposed box is rarely perfect.\n",
    "\n",
    "Initial proposal:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "(x=50,y=30,w=100,h=120)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "True object:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "(x=45,y=25,w=115,h=130)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Regression learns corrections:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Δx=-5\n",
    "Δy=-5\n",
    "Δw=15\n",
    "Δh=10\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Refined result:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "(45,25,115,130)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This improves localization accuracy.\n"
   ]
