    "## Example Workthrough\n",
    "\n",
    "**Detecting Animals in an Image**\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose we have this image:\n",
    "\n",
    "* a dog sitting on grass\n",
    "* a ball nearby\n",
    "\n",
    "### Region Proposals\n",
    "\n",
    "Selective Search creates 2000 candidate boxes.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Proposal | Possible Content |\n",
    "| -------- | ---------------- |\n",
    "| Box A    | Dog face         |\n",
    "| Box B    | Whole dog        |\n",
    "| Box C    | Ball             |\n",
    "| Box D    | Grass only       |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Resize Each Proposal\n",
    "\n",
    "Each region becomes:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "227 \\times 227\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### CNN Feature Extraction\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN extracts features.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Dog region features\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN learns patterns such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "* fur texture\n",
    "* ears\n",
    "* eyes\n",
    "* body shape\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Ball region features\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN learns:\n",
    "\n",
    "* circular shape\n",
    "* color patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "The SVM classifiers output scores.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Region | Dog Score | Ball Score | Background |\n",
    "| ------ | --------- | ---------- | ---------- |\n",
    "| A      | 0.95      | 0.01       | 0.04       |\n",
    "| B      | 0.98      | 0.00       | 0.02       |\n",
    "| C      | 0.02      | 0.91       | 0.07       |\n",
    "| D      | 0.01      | 0.00       | 0.99       |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS)\n",
    "\n",
    "Many boxes overlap around the same object.\n",
    "\n",
    "R-CNN keeps the best one.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "* 5 boxes around dog\n",
    "* Keep highest confidence box\n",
    "* Remove duplicates\n",
    "\n",
    "This process is called:\n",
    "\n",
    "### Final Output\n",
    "\n",
    "The system outputs:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Dog — 98%\n",
    "Ball — 91%\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "with final bounding boxes.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Evolution After R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fast R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Improved speed by:\n",
    "\n",
    "* running CNN only once on full image\n",
    "* extracting region features from feature maps\n",
    "\n",
    "Much faster.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Faster R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Introduced:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Region Proposal Network (RPN)\n",
    "\n",
    "No need for Selective Search.\n",
    "\n",
    "Real-time-ish performance.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mask R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Extended Faster R-CNN by adding:\n",
    "\n",
    "* pixel-level segmentation masks\n",
    "\n",
    "Used in advanced vision tasks.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method       | Proposal Method               | Speed       |\n",
    "| ------------ | ----------------------------- | ----------- |\n",
    "| R-CNN        | Selective Search              | Slow        |\n",
    "| Fast R-CNN   | Selective Search + shared CNN | Faster      |\n",
    "| Faster R-CNN | RPN                           | Much Faster |\n",
    "| Mask R-CNN   | RPN + masks                   | Advanced    |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Charecterstics\n",
    "\n",
    "### Advantages:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Much higher accuracy than traditional methods\n",
    "    * Older methods: `HOG + sliding windows`\n",
    "    * R-CNN learned deep features automatically.\n",
    "2. Reduced exhaustive search\n",
    "    * Instead of millions of windows: `Only ~2000 proposals`\n",
    "3. CNN feature learning\n",
    "    * Deep features outperform hand-crafted features.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Limitations of R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Very slow\n",
    "    * For each image: `2000 CNN forward passes`\n",
    "    * Each proposal is processed independently. Time: `≈47 seconds/image` (on original hardware)\n",
    "2. Large storage requirement\n",
    "    * Extracted features were stored on disk: `hundreds of GB`\n",
    "3. Multi-stage training\n",
    "    * CNN + SVM + regression trained separately. Complex pipeline.\n",
    "4. No end-to-end learning\n",
    "    * Entire system is not optimized jointly.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mathematical Perspective\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN learns a function:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "f(x) \\rightarrow y\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "\n",
    "* x = image region\n",
    "* y = feature representation or class probabilities\n",
    "\n",
    "For classification, the softmax function is often used:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "P(y_i)=\\frac{e^{z_i}}{\\sum_j e^{z_j}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "This converts scores into probabilities.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "> “Use CNNs on proposed object regions instead of scanning everything.”\n",
    "\n",
    "Its major innovations:\n",
    "\n",
    "* region proposals\n",
    "* CNN feature extraction\n",
    "* object-wise classification\n",
    "\n",
    "Even though newer methods are faster, R-CNN is historically very important in modern Computer Vision and deep learning.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fast R-CNN \n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN is an improved version of R-CNN introduced by Ross Girshick in 2015. It was designed to solve the major weaknesses of R-CNN:\n",
    "\n",
    "* Extremely slow training\n",
    "* Extremely slow testing\n",
    "* Large storage requirements\n",
    "* Multi-stage pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "The key idea of Fast R-CNN is:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Instead of running a CNN separately for each proposed region, run the CNN **once on the entire image**, then extract features for each region from the shared feature map.\n",
    "\n",
    "This simple change dramatically increased speed.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why R-CNN Was Slow\n",
    "\n",
    "Recall R-CNN workflow:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Image\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Selective Search → 2000 proposals\n",
    "   ↓\n",
    "Crop proposal 1 → CNN(AlexNet)\n",
    "Crop proposal 2 → CNN(AlexNet)\n",
    "Crop proposal 3 → CNN(AlexNet)\n",
    "...\n",
    "Crop proposal 2000 → CNN(AlexNet)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Problem:\n",
    "\n",
    "For one image:\n",
    "\n",
    "* ~2000 proposals\n",
    "* CNN executed ~2000 times\n",
    "\n",
    "Large redundant computation occurs because neighboring proposals overlap heavily.\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Proposal A: dog\n",
    "Proposal B: slightly shifted dog\n",
    "Proposal C: larger dog box\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The CNN repeatedly extracts almost identical features. Fast R-CNN removes this redundancy.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Fast R-CNN Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "![Fast R-CNN Architecture](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/masum184e/handbook-old/removed/images/cnn/fast_r_cnn.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "Pipeline:\n",
    "1. Input Image\n",
    "2. Region proposal generation\n",
    "      * Selective Search(~2000 region proposals)\n",
    "3. CNN feature extraction from whole image\n",
    "4. Feature Map\n",
    "5. ROI Pooling\n",
    "6. Fully connected layers\n",
    "7. Softmax classifier\n",
    "8. Bounding box regression\n",
    "9. Final detections\n",
    "\n",
    "> Major difference: CNN runs **once per image**, not once per proposal.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Region proposal generation\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose image: `Dog sitting beside bicycle`\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600×600\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Selective Search still generates: `2000 region proposals`\n",
    "\n",
    "Example proposals:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "R1 = dog\n",
    "R2 = bicycle\n",
    "R3 = sky\n",
    "R4 = grass\n",
    "...\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike R-CNN, we do not crop them individually.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Entire Image Passes Through CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Whole image enters CNN:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600×600\n",
    "$$\n",
    "CNN performs:\n",
    "\n",
    "* convolutions\n",
    "* ReLU\n",
    "* pooling\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose CNN reduces dimensions:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600×600×3 \\\\\n",
    "$$\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\downarrow \\\\\n",
    "$$\n",
    "$$\n",
    "37×37×512\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Output: `Feature map`\n",
    "$$\n",
    "37×37×512\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This feature map contains learned visual information.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Backbone CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN uses a **backbone CNN** to extract visual features from the entire image.\n",
    "\n",
    "A backbone is a pre-trained convolutional neural network such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "* VGG16\n",
    "* AlexNet\n",
    "* ResNet\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of running CNN separately for every region proposal like R-CNN, Fast R-CNN passes the whole image through the backbone only once.\n",
    "\n",
    "Input image:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600 \\times 600 \\times 3\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "After convolution and pooling operations inside the backbone:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600 \\times 600 \\times 3\n",
    "$$\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\downarrow\n",
    "$$\n",
    "$$\n",
    "37 \\times 37 \\times 512\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Output:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "37 \\times 37 \\times 512\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This output is called the **feature map**.\n",
    "\n",
    "The backbone learns important visual patterns such as:\n",
    "\n",
    "* edges\n",
    "* textures\n",
    "* shapes\n",
    "* object parts\n",
    "\n",
    "The generated feature map is reused for all ROI proposals, which makes Fast R-CNN significantly faster than R-CNN.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Common Backbones**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Model   | Usage                        |\n",
    "| ------- | ---------------------------- |\n",
    "| AlexNet | Early CNN backbone           |\n",
    "| VGG16   | Original Fast R-CNN backbone |\n",
    "| ResNet  | Modern object detectors      |\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Why Feature Maps Help\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose image contains:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Dog at center\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "The feature map preserves spatial information. Each location in feature map corresponds to a region in original image.\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus instead of repeatedly recomputing CNN features:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Compute once\n",
    "- Reuse many times\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the central innovation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### ROI (Region of Interest) Projection\n",
    "\n",
    "We have proposal coordinates from Selective Search:\n",
    "\n",
    "Example: Original image(Dog box)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(150,200,300,400)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Need to locate corresponding area in feature map:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "37×37 \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Scaling:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "600→37\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Scale factor:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\frac{37}{600}=.0617\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Projected coordinates:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(9,12,18,25)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Now ROI exists inside feature map.\n",
    "\n",
    "### ROI Pooling Layer\n",
    "\n",
    "Different proposals have different sizes:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "ROI1: 8×9\n",
    "ROI2: 5×15\n",
    "ROI3: 20×10\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Fully connected layers require fixed input size. Fast R-CNN introduces **ROI Pooling**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "Convert variable-size regions into fixed-size output.\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose output size:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "7×7\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "#### ROI Pooling Procedure\n",
    "\n",
    "Example ROI:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "14×14\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Divide into:\n",
    "$$\n",
    "7×7\n",
    "$$\n",
    "grids\n",
    "\n",
    "Each grid:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "2×2\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Apply max pooling.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Grid values:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "1 4\n",
    "3 2\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Max:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "4\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Repeat for all cells.\n",
    "\n",
    "Output:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "7×7 \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "fixed representation\n",
    "\n",
    "Now every ROI has same size.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Fully Connected Layers\n",
    "\n",
    "ROI pooled output:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "7×7×512\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Flatten: `25088 values`\n",
    "\n",
    "Pass into fully connected layers. CNN learns high-level object information:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "ears\n",
    "wheels\n",
    "legs\n",
    "windows\n",
    "textures\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Softmax Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "* Unlike R-CNN: SVM classifiers\n",
    "* Fast R-CNN uses: Softmax layer\n",
    "\n",
    "Output:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Dog = .92\n",
    "Cat=.03\n",
    "Bike=.88\n",
    "Background=.01\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose proposal:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "R1\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Prediction:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Dog\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Bounding Box Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "Proposal boxes are imperfect.\n",
    "\n",
    "Initial:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "(100,100,180,200)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Ground truth:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "(95,98,190,205)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Model predicts corrections:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "Δx=-5\n",
    "Δy=-2\n",
    "Δw=10\n",
    "Δh=5\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Refined output:\n",
    "\n",
    "```text\n",
    "(95,98,190,205)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Localization improves.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Multi-Task Loss in Fast R-CNN\n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN combines:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Classification loss\n",
    "2. Localization loss\n",
    "\n",
    "Loss:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "Total Loss = Classification Loss + Bounding Box Loss\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This enables end-to-end training.\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike R-CNN:\n",
    "\n",
    "* CNN\n",
    "* SVM\n",
    "* Regression\n",
    "\n",
    "trained separately.\n",
    "\n",
    "Fast R-CNN jointly trains everything."
   ]
